16:34.201 --> 16:37.663
Liberty Belle's been training for weeks.
Are you worried?

16:38.580 --> 16:41.542
No! It's gonna be a day at the beach.

16:41.625 --> 16:43.711
-[audience groaning]
-[man] Oh, come on!

16:43.836 --> 16:47.172
Get up, you coward! Get up and fight!

16:47.965 --> 16:49.008
[slurps]

16:49.091 --> 16:51.427
[grunting] Oh, I'm mad!

16:52.261 --> 16:54.930
Look at this chicken!

16:55.014 --> 16:56.765
[audience clucking]

16:56.849 --> 17:01.478
You're scared to fight me
'cause you know you'll lose.

17:02.062 --> 17:04.314
You haven't wrestled in months.

17:04.898 --> 17:10.070
Can you even move, chicken?
[laughs, clucking]

17:13.615 --> 17:15.117
[Tammé grunts]

17:15.826 --> 17:16.952
[audience clucking]

17:17.036 --> 17:19.246
[Bash] The audience is starting
to get into it.

17:19.329 --> 17:23.250
We got cluckers, ladies and gentlemen.
Cluck, cluck b'guck.

17:23.876 --> 17:27.046
They're all doing it.
We're a family of McNuggets!

17:27.129 --> 17:28.797
We're all chickens together.

17:28.881 --> 17:29.798
[screams]

17:30.382 --> 17:34.344
[Bash]
Oh! A lawn chair shot to the back. Whoa!

17:34.428 --> 17:39.683
That chair broke like a pile of twigs,
sponsored by Patio Town!

17:39.767 --> 17:41.769
[both grunting]

17:43.520 --> 17:45.481
-[Keith] Ring the bell.
-[bell rings]

17:45.606 --> 17:49.777
[Bash] Well, it looks like Welfare Queen
is not giving up her crown tonight, folks.

17:50.652 --> 17:53.113
Liberty Belle might have to take
a rain check.

17:53.197 --> 17:55.783
And we all know that check's gonna bounce.

17:55.866 --> 17:57.868
This is my house!

17:58.869 --> 18:00.913
-My house!
-Ref, help!

18:01.663 --> 18:02.623
[Debbie] Oh!

18:02.706 --> 18:07.628
[Bash] Whoa, Welfare Queen's moves are
dirtier than the nethers of a street cat.

18:07.711 --> 18:08.837
-[Keith] Wanna give up?
-No!

18:08.921 --> 18:11.090
-[Tammé] Ah, you like that?
-Do you wanna quit?

18:11.173 --> 18:12.758
-[Tammé] Do you like that?
-Never!

18:12.925 --> 18:14.760
-[Tammé] All right!
-[screams]

18:14.843 --> 18:18.889
[Keith] Talk to me. You wanna quit?
One, two... Just two.

18:19.807 --> 18:22.267
-Two. Let's get off them ropes.
-[Debbie groans]

18:24.436 --> 18:25.562
[shouts]

18:25.813 --> 18:26.855
[grunts]

18:30.734 --> 18:31.568
Crucifix!

18:31.985 --> 18:35.030
The power of Christ compels you!

18:35.114 --> 18:37.783
[Keith] Wanna give up?
It's about 30 seconds.

18:39.660 --> 18:41.120
One, two...

18:41.203 --> 18:42.412
[Debbie] Come on!

18:42.496 --> 18:43.413
Just two.

18:43.914 --> 18:47.793
Well, ladies and gentlemen,
epic battles don't end quickly.

18:47.876 --> 18:49.419
-[groans]
-[Tammé] Yeah!

18:51.213 --> 18:52.548
[exclaims]

18:53.507 --> 18:54.383
One!

18:55.092 --> 18:57.010
[Tammé] Look at all that pretty hair.

18:57.094 --> 19:01.431
[Keith] Hey, hey! Get off that hair!
I'm gonna count. One! Two!

19:01.515 --> 19:03.642
-Three! Four!
-Rip it from the roots!

19:03.725 --> 19:06.562
[audience booing]

19:06.645 --> 19:08.647
Wake up, Barbie.

19:08.730 --> 19:10.149
[screaming]

19:12.818 --> 19:16.280
-[Keith] Go to the corner, woman.
-I'm about to cash my check.

19:16.864 --> 19:20.367
-Cha-ching!
-[screaming]

19:23.162 --> 19:24.496
[Tammé mutters]

19:24.580 --> 19:27.916
Mama spanks her kid! Ha!

19:30.085 --> 19:33.839
[Keith] One, two. Just two. Just got two.

19:33.922 --> 19:37.134
[both groaning]

19:40.429 --> 19:42.264
I do this for y'all.

19:42.848 --> 19:44.558
You mean everything to me.

19:47.352 --> 19:50.397
Let's finish this, Ref,
and go home to our families.

19:51.440 --> 19:53.567
[Keith]
Watch that hair. Let go of that hair.

19:53.650 --> 19:57.070
I have a feeling the tides are about
to turn.

19:59.615 --> 20:01.283
All right, Tammé, you okay?

20:01.658 --> 20:03.869
Ready? Are you gonna do this or what?
Hey.

20:04.411 --> 20:05.370
Are we doing this?

20:07.372 --> 20:09.082
Let's go. Let's go home.

20:12.294 --> 20:15.088
Ugh! [groans]

20:15.881 --> 20:19.051
-Oh!
-Liberty Belle's got a question for y'all.

20:19.468 --> 20:23.222
How do you spell "freedom"?

20:26.558 --> 20:27.684
[both grunt]

20:29.478 --> 20:30.520
[both grunt]

20:31.813 --> 20:33.398
-[grunts]
-[groans]

20:33.482 --> 20:34.566
[cheering loudly]

20:35.692 --> 20:36.693
Get up!

20:36.860 --> 20:37.903
[grunts]

20:39.738 --> 20:41.073
[panting]

20:45.077 --> 20:47.246
-[grunting]
-[shouts]

20:50.374 --> 20:52.376
[grunts, groans]

20:55.087 --> 20:57.506
[Keith] One, two, three!

20:58.048 --> 21:01.510
And that's it!
The Queen has finally fallen.

21:01.593 --> 21:03.720
-[Debbie exclaims]
-[Bash] The winner of the match

21:03.804 --> 21:05.264
and the crown,

21:05.347 --> 21:09.017
our one and only Liberty Belle!

21:10.102 --> 21:11.687
[laughs]

21:13.480 --> 21:17.526
-[hums] <i>♪ You're the queen ♪</i>
-Yay!

21:18.110 --> 21:22.197
[Bash] Liberty Belle, what a match.
How are you feeling?

21:22.322 --> 21:26.326
I'd like to dedicate my victory
to all the mothers out there.

21:26.410 --> 21:27.327
[Bash] Wow!

21:27.661 --> 21:31.206
Even you, Welfare Queen.
I know you're a mother, too.

21:31.290 --> 21:34.418
-[booing]
-No, y'all, it's true.

21:34.543 --> 21:37.546
She has many, many kids.

21:37.629 --> 21:39.006
[audience laughing]

21:39.089 --> 21:41.091
But I have hope in my heart.

21:41.258 --> 21:45.012
I believe even the worst among us
can be transformed.

21:45.345 --> 21:49.975
That's why I got Welfare Queen
an entry-level position

21:50.225 --> 21:53.937
at my favorite local fast-food restaurant.

21:55.063 --> 21:58.483
Who wants Welfare Queen to get a job?

21:58.567 --> 22:01.737
[Debbie and audience chanting]
Get a job! Get a job!

22:01.820 --> 22:04.656
Get a job! Get a job!

22:04.990 --> 22:07.868
Get a job! Get a job!

22:07.951 --> 22:10.787
Get a job! Get a job!

22:10.912 --> 22:13.957
Get a job! Get a job!

22:14.041 --> 22:16.585
Get a job! Get a job!

22:16.710 --> 22:19.504
Get a job! Get a job!

22:19.629 --> 22:22.466
Get a job! Get a job!

22:22.591 --> 22:26.595
-Get a job! Get a job! Get a job!
-[whimpers]

22:26.678 --> 22:28.472
Get a job.

22:31.725 --> 22:36.605
Uh... [clears throat]
Our new champ, Liberty Belle!

22:39.524 --> 22:41.026
Give it up, y'all.

22:41.109 --> 22:42.736
-[scattered applause]
-Wow!

22:44.946 --> 22:46.073
Shit.

22:50.285 --> 22:52.371
Liberty Belle, uh, why don't you

22:52.454 --> 22:55.999
tell the audience more
about your lovable daughter?

22:57.042 --> 23:00.420
As y'all know, I fight every match
for my little girl.

23:01.171 --> 23:03.048
[stammers] Savannah Rose.

23:03.131 --> 23:05.801
-[Bash] Oh, Savannah Rose. How relatable.
-[audience clamoring]

23:05.884 --> 23:08.720
[Debbie] Yes, I-- I'm just like y'all.

23:08.804 --> 23:11.473
[man] Long live Welfare Queen!

23:11.556 --> 23:15.519
Whoa! Someone get that jack-o-lantern out
of here. Hey!

23:19.648 --> 23:21.650
[upbeat music playing]

23:22.401 --> 23:23.402
Hey, what are you doing?

23:23.485 --> 23:27.280
-I'm with the show. Can I borrow her?
-[woman] Sure, okay. It's okay, honey.

23:27.364 --> 23:28.740
Now, yell Mommy at her. Scream.

23:28.824 --> 23:30.492
-Mommy!
-Liberty Belle.

23:31.993 --> 23:33.870
[in Russian accent] I have your daughter!

23:36.123 --> 23:37.374
Savannah Rose!

23:38.583 --> 23:42.212
No one move! I have shashka,

23:42.546 --> 23:45.757
Russian saber behind my back.

23:46.258 --> 23:48.552
If anyone try follow me,

23:48.635 --> 23:51.847
little girl eat sword!

23:53.932 --> 23:56.852
Zoya, why are you doing this?

23:58.019 --> 24:00.439
We have unfinished business.

24:00.772 --> 24:03.859
You cannot ignore Zoya!

24:04.484 --> 24:07.404
If you want to see
sniveling runt alive again,

24:07.904 --> 24:10.907
you have to fight me! [cackling]

24:10.991 --> 24:12.117
Mommy!

24:14.619 --> 24:15.495
[Ruth] One more time.

24:15.579 --> 24:17.205
-Mommy!
-[Ruth shouts]

24:17.289 --> 24:21.001
Well, this match has taken
a heartbreaking twist,

24:21.084 --> 24:22.127
ladies and gentlemen.

24:22.210 --> 24:26.715
Liberty Belle wins the crown,
but loses her daughter.

24:26.882 --> 24:29.885
And what's a mother without a child?

24:30.093 --> 24:32.095
Just a person.

24:33.138 --> 24:37.184
-[man] Don't let her get away!
-[screams] No!

24:37.684 --> 24:41.313
My daughter! [sobs]

24:45.817 --> 24:49.321
[audience chanting] Liberty Belle!
Liberty Belle! Liberty Belle!

24:53.617 --> 24:55.619
[sighs]

24:57.204 --> 24:58.288
You're here.

25:02.209 --> 25:03.376
[Tammé sniffles]

25:09.424 --> 25:10.383
You okay?

25:11.259 --> 25:14.304
Of course. It's all planned out.
No one actually gets hurt.

25:14.387 --> 25:15.847
I didn't mean the wrestling.

25:19.893 --> 25:22.646
I'm okay. I just wasn't ready
for you to see all that.

25:23.063 --> 25:23.897
It felt...

25:24.773 --> 25:27.192
different with you watching.

25:30.820 --> 25:31.696
So, what'd you think?

25:33.823 --> 25:35.033
What did I think?

25:37.369 --> 25:38.286
Okay.

25:39.788 --> 25:42.666
I thought it was...

25:44.167 --> 25:45.544
[chuckles] ...offensive.

25:46.753 --> 25:50.215
I mean, you were right, it was offensive.
Definitely, offensive.

25:53.510 --> 25:54.970
I can't believe you did that.

25:55.971 --> 25:56.888
Wrestling.

25:58.181 --> 26:00.100
I mean, you threw a white girl
across a ring...

26:05.355 --> 26:08.608
When did you get that strong?
I don't think I've ever seen you exercise.

26:12.487 --> 26:15.448
[chuckles]
Chasing your chubby behind around.

26:15.782 --> 26:18.868
Carrying you here and there.
"Mommy, up! Mommy, no walk!"

26:19.494 --> 26:21.454
That's all the exercise I needed.

26:22.998 --> 26:24.916
Did you eat anything before that match?

26:25.834 --> 26:29.087
-Uh, I had a muffin.
-That's not dinner. You--

26:31.256 --> 26:32.382
I'm taking you out.

26:33.633 --> 26:36.177
-Oh?
-It's still parents' weekend.

26:36.344 --> 26:38.471
We got to do something normal.

26:39.431 --> 26:41.349
[Tammé] Okay, look at you!

26:43.727 --> 26:44.894
Thank you.

26:46.605 --> 26:48.064
I'm kinda scared of you now.

26:48.189 --> 26:52.193
You should be. I'm a former champion.
[laughs]

27:21.431 --> 27:23.016
I made a few changes.

27:24.976 --> 27:29.147
So I call you about the bed,
and you sell all the furniture.

27:29.856 --> 27:33.068
Are you crazy? Where's Randy gonna sit?
Where's he gonna eat?

27:33.151 --> 27:34.486
Don't worry about Randy.

27:34.569 --> 27:36.946
I worry about Randy all the time.

27:37.405 --> 27:40.116
I think about how he's gonna feel
having two houses.

27:40.200 --> 27:43.745
I was trying to get my place ready
so it felt more familiar for him.

27:44.162 --> 27:46.623
[sighs] Oh.

27:46.706 --> 27:48.792
Jesus Christ, Debbie, you...

27:49.501 --> 27:51.711
You always take everything too far.

27:51.795 --> 27:53.004
It is always about you.

27:53.088 --> 27:55.590
Do you ever think
about the person on the other side?

27:56.341 --> 27:57.926
Are you calling me a bad mother?

27:58.968 --> 27:59.886
I didn't say that.

28:05.684 --> 28:08.061
He ate. He crawled around the floor.

28:08.853 --> 28:10.730
We read the book about the moon.

28:10.814 --> 28:13.274
We said good night
to everything in the room.

28:14.984 --> 28:16.027
And I'm going home.

28:20.573 --> 28:21.408
Good night, Mark.

28:22.450 --> 28:23.410
Good night.

